comment.text: This translation key is used to display a success message when an item has been moved to a new location. The message includes the title of the moved item and the name of its destination folder. It appears as a pop-up or toast notification after completing a file move operation in the application.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The word 'uğurla' (successfully) is placed awkwardly in the sentence. A more natural phrasing would be to place it before 'köçürüldü'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: <2>{{title}}</2> uğurla <1>{{folderName}}</1> qovluğuna köçürüldü should be <2>{{title}}</2> <1>{{folderName}}</1> qovluğuna uğurla köçürüldü.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The verb "přesunuto" (moved) should agree in gender with the noun "title". Since "title" is masculine, the past participle should be "přesunuto".
The word 'moved' should be translated as 'déplacé' or 'transféré'. 'Déplacé' is more common in this context.

The verb 'moved' should be in the past tense. 'spostato' (moved) is correct, but the sentence structure implies an ongoing action. A better phrasing would be 'è stato spostato' (has been moved) to clearly indicate a completed action.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: <2>{{title}}</2> è stato spostato con successo in <1>{{folderName}}</1>

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Japanese translation includes the particle 'は' after the title, which might make the sentence sound slightly less natural in this context. While grammatically correct, it's less common in system messages.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: <2>{{title}}</2> を <1>{{folderName}}</1> に正常に移動されました

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The use of 이/가 is ambiguous and grammatically awkward in this context. It should be replaced with a more appropriate particle.
The phrase "ຢ່າງສໍາເລັດແລ້ວ" translates to "successfully" but might sound slightly formal or overly emphatic in this context. A more natural phrasing for "successfully moved" could be considered.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider alternatives like "ໄດ້ລຽງການໂຍກຍ້າຍໄປສູ່" or simply removing the phrase altogether if the action implies success.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The placement of the angle brackets in the Polish translation doesn't match the English source. The numbering is reversed.

The translation ' සාර්ථකව <1>{{folderName}}</1> වෙත ගෙනයන ලදී.' is a bit awkward. A more natural phrasing would be something like ' <1>{{folderName}}</1> වෙත යවා ඇත'.  'ගෙන යන ලදී' implies 'being carried' which isn't ideal for a digital file movement.

The passive voice "uspešno premaknjeno" is grammatically correct, but may sound less natural in this context. A more active voice, like 'uspešno prestavljeno' (successfully moved) might be more appropriate depending on the tone.

The English phrase 'successfully moved to' is not perfectly translated. 'başarıyla taşındı' is a literal translation and while understandable, it could be more naturally phrased. A better option would be '... konumuna taşındı'.
